===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|de|en}} ''[[Antisemitismus]]'', which was coined in 1879 by German political agitator [[w:Wilhelm Marr|Wilhelm Marr]] to replace ''Judenhass'' ("Jew-hatred") to make hatred of the Jews seem rational and sanctioned by scientific knowledge. The similar term ''antisemitisch'' ("anti-semitic") was first used in 1860, by Jewish scholar [[w:Moritz Steinschneider|Moritz Steinschneider]]. See [[w: Antisemitism#Etymology and usage|Wikipedia's article on the etymology and usage of the term]].

